WEBVTT

00:00.160 --> 00:03.680
Kruija is one of the most mentioned cities in Albanian history.

00:04.720 --> 00:10.640
Kruija lies on the slope of the Kruija mountain, at an altitude of 608 meters above sea level.

00:11.760 --> 00:16.480
Archaeological excavation in the castle of Kruija testifies that the city has been an

00:16.480 --> 00:22.560
Illyrian settlement since 3rd century BC. The village of Zgirtjes, situated in the

00:22.560 --> 00:26.880
vicinities of the city, is thought to be the antique city of Albanopolis,

00:26.880 --> 00:33.040
mentioned by Ptolemaeus in the 2nd century AD. The settlement of Zgirtjes was abandoned

00:33.040 --> 00:37.120
at the beginning of the Middle Ages and its inhabitants found a better protected place

00:37.120 --> 00:42.160
in Kruija by making it this way, the center of the Arboresh culture as it has been testified

00:42.160 --> 00:48.960
also by the objects found in a cemetery dated 6th to 8th century AD. The city is mentioned

00:48.960 --> 00:55.680
for the first time as an episcopal center in a document of 879. Kruija was the center of

00:55.680 --> 01:02.080
the Byzantine garrisons and Byzantine governors until the end of the 12th century. Moreover,

01:02.080 --> 01:08.880
Kruija was the capital of the first Albanian feudal state, 1191,215.

01:10.000 --> 01:16.720
The city flourishes in the 13th and 14th centuries. In the second half of the 14th century,

01:16.720 --> 01:21.280
it is the center of Topii's family with a highly developed trade and craftsmanship.

01:21.280 --> 01:26.080
The houses close to the castle are the oldest which date that time.

